Package: linguisticsdown
Title: Easy Linguistics Document Writing with R Markdown
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Yongfu", "Liao", , "liao961120@gmail.com", c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Provide Shiny gadget to search, type, and insert IPA symbols into 
    documents or scripts, requiring only knowledge about phonetics or X-SAMPA.
    Also provide functions to facilitate rendering of IPA symbols in 
    LaTeX and PDF format, making IPA symbols properly rendered in all output formats.
    A minimal R Markdown template for authoring Linguistics related documents is also provided.
URL: https://liao961120.github.io/linguisticsdown/, https://github.com/liao961120/linguisticsdown
BugReports: https://github.com/liao961120/linguisticsdown/issues
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: dplyr,
    stringr,
    tidyr,
    shiny,
    magrittr,
    miniUI,
    knitr,
    rstudioapi,
    DT
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
Suggests: pkgdown,
    rmarkdown
